The solution I came used was this:

         final String fieldName = &quot;UnknowFieldName&quot;;
         thrown.expect(MasterCatalogueBadMergeDataException.class);
         thrown.expect(hasProperty(&quot;cause&quot;,
instanceOf(ModelUnknownFieldException.class)));
         thrown.expect(hasProperty(&quot;cause&quot;, hasProperty(&quot;detailMessage&quot;,
is(&quot;Field &#39;&quot; + fieldName + &quot;&#39; does not exist.&quot;))));
         thrown.expectMessage(is(&quot;The field &#39;&quot; + fieldName + &quot;&#39; is not
recognised.&quot;));

It&#39;s a bit of a mouth-full, but seems to do the trick.

(I&#39;m too scared to try and write a custom Hamcrest matcher)

